  "exploit_path": {
    "summary": "The attack was initiated from address 0x8f921e27e3af106015d1c3a244ec4f48dbfcad14 via transaction 0xa9df1bd97cf6d4d1d58d3adfbdde719e46a1548db724c2e76b4cd4c3222f22b3. Forensic evidence from the DeFiHackLabs repository, which contains a proof-of-concept file named 'HYDT_exp.sol', indicates the target was likely the HYDT protocol. The attack involved interactions with core BSC infrastructure including WBNB (0xbb4CdB9CBd36B01bD1cBaEBF2De08d9173bc095c), USDT (0x55d398326f99059fF775485246999027B3197955), and the PancakeSwap Router (0x10ED43C718714eb63d5aA57B78B54704E256024E), suggesting the attacker manipulated token prices through DEX-based mechanisms. The attacker likely exploited vulnerabilities in the protocol's price oracle or token pricing logic to extract value.",
